7.pdf |accessdate=November 5, 2013}}</ref>\n||{{nts|1763}}\n||[[Gujarat]], [[India]]\n||February 2002\n||March 2002\n|1 month\n||Minimum death toll includes 790 [[Muslim]] death toll. Both death tolls include 254 [[Hindu]] deaths. Maximum death toll includes 223 presumed mixing as dead, and a higher 2,500 Muslim death toll.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n|-\n||[[Genocide of Shias by ISIL]]\n||{{nts|Tens of thousands}}<ref>\"Which groups are under threat by ISIS in Iraq?\", cnn.com. Retrieved December 22, 2015.</ref>\n||{{nts|Tens of thousands}}\n||{{nts|Tens of thousands}}\n||[[Iraq]], [[Syria]], [[Afghanistan]]\n||2003\n||present\n|16 years\n||[[Ethnic cleansing]], execution, forced conversion, rape, and enslavement of [[Shias]] by [[ISIL]]. One of the first instances was the [[Imam Ali Mosque bombing]] in [[Najaf]]\n|-\n||[[Conquest of the Desert]]\n||{{nts|1300}}\n||{{nts|1300}}\n||{{nts|1300}}\n||[[Argentina]]\n||Mid 1870s\n||1884\n|?\n||Military campaign, directed mainly by General [[Julio Argentino Roca]], which established Argentine dominance over [[Patagonia]], then inhabited by [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas#Argentina|indigenous peoples]].<ref name=\"auto\">Carlos A. Floria and C\u00e9sar A. Garc\u00eda Belsunce, 1971. ''Historia de los Argentinos'' I and II; {{ISBN|84-599-5081-6}}. {{Page needed|date=December 2008}}</ref>\u2013 Part of the [[Native American Genocide|Genocide of indigenous peoples in the Americas]]\n|-\n||[[Genocide of Christians by ISIL]]\n||{{nts|Thousands}}<ref>\"As Christians Flee, Governments Pressured To Declare ISIS Guilty Of Genocide\". NPR. December 24, 2015. \"At least a thousand Christians have been killed. Hundreds of thousands have fled.\"</ref>\n||{{nts|Thousands}}\n||{{nts|Thousands}}\n||Worldwide\n||2014\n||present\n|4 years\n||[[Ethnic cleansing]], execution, forced conversion, rape, and enslavement of [[Christians]] by [[ISIL]]. In Iraq, the genocide started before 2014, as exemplified by the [[2010 Baghdad chu