2/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/1673249.stm|title=Croatian holocaust still stirs controversy|date=November 29, 2001 |accessdate=September 29, 2010 |work=BBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc1\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4479837.stm|title=Balkan 'Auschwitz' haunts Croatia|date=April 25, 2005 |accessdate=September 29, 2010 |work=BBC News|quote=No one really knows how many died here. Serbs talk of 700,000. Most estimates put the figure nearer 100,000.}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kolyma#Accounts of the Kolyma Gulag camps|Kolyma]]\n|{{nts|130000}}\n|{{nts|500000}}\n|{{nts|254951}}\n|[[Kolyma]], [[Soviet Union]]\n|1932\n|1954\n|22 years\n|<ref>Ludwik Kowalski: Alaska notes on Stalinism. Retrieved January 18, 2007. Case Study: Stalin's Purges from Genderside Watch. Retrieved January 19, 2007. George Bien, Gulag Survivor in the ''[[Boston Globe]]'', June 22, 2005, [[Kolyma]].</ref>\n|-\n|[[Stutthof|Stutthof concentration camp]]\n|{{nts|85000}}\n|{{nts|85000}}\n|{{nts|85000}}\n|[[Stutthof]], [[Poland]]\n|1939\n|1945\n|6 years\n|See also: [[Nazi Germany|Second World War]]\n|-\n|[[Stara Gradi\u0161ka concentration camp]]\n|{{nts|12790}}\n|{{nts|75000}}\n|{{nts|30972}}\n|[[Croatia]]\n|1941\n|1945\n|4 years\n|Primarily for women and children.<ref name=\"Smreka\">{{cite web|url=http://public.mzos.hr/fgs.axd?id=13416|title=STARA GRADI\u0160KA Usta\u0161ki koncentracijski logor|author=Jelka Smreka|publisher=Spomen podru\u010dja Jasenovac|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717120002/http://public.mzos.hr/fgs.axd?id=13416|archivedate=July 17, 2011 |url-status=dead|accessdate=August 25, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"kovacic\">{{cite web|url=http://hrcak.srce.hr/file/75758|title=Iskapanja na prostoru koncentracijskog logora Stara Gradi\u0161ka i procjena broj \u017ertava|author=Davor Kova\u010di\u0107|year=2004|accessdate=August 25, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum|Tuol Sleng]]\n|{{nts|17000}}\n|{{nts|17000}}\n|{{nts|17000}}\n|[[Phnom Penh]], [[Cambod